<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-03-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-03-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="844" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Grip</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-03-11"><hi rend="italic">March 11,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I had the honor to
                            receive yesterday afternoon your note of the 9th instant, requesting the
                            good offices of this Government for the Norwegian steamship <hi rend="italic">Hugin</hi> upon her arrival at the port of Macoris,
                            Santo Domingo.</p>
                        <p>In reply it gives me pleasure to say that I have already brought this
                            matter to the attention of the Navy Department, having communicated <pb facs="0901" n="813" xml:id="pg_813"/> to that Department yesterday a
                            request of Messrs. Hugh Kelly &amp; Co. for the protection of the
                            steamship <hi rend="italic">Hugin</hi>.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>